HEADWORD: Adustion
<hw>A*dus"tion</hw> <pr>(?; 106)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>adustio</ets>, fr. <ets>adurere</ets>, <ets>adustum</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>adustion</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of burning, or
heating to dryness; the state of being thus heated or dried.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Harvey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>Cauterization.</def>
